NIH Launches Effort To Speed Up Development Of COVID-19 TreatmentsEnlarge this image toggle caption Matt Rourke/AP Matt Rourke/APIn an bid to help speed up the development of potential treatment options and a vaccine for COVID-19, the National Institutes of Health on Friday announced a new public-private research partnership.
Among the companies participating in the effort are Pfizer, Johnson & Johnson and Merck.
The announcement comes after President Trump and public health officials on Thursday unveiled new guidelines for states to begin reopening the country.
Health experts say that in order to safely do that, there needs to be more testing, contact tracing and better drugs to treat COVID-19.
Just to report, yesterday although not yet peer reviewed, that in a monkey model it looked as if this did provide benefit for COVID-19.